title: White Rock Township, McDonald County, Missouri
text:
White Rock Township is an inactive <a href="civil%20township">township</a> in <a href="McDonald%20County%2C%20Missouri">McDonald County</a>, in the <a href="U.S.%20state">U.S. state</a> of <a href="Missouri">Missouri</a>.
White Rock Township was established in 1867, and named for deposits of white limestone within its borders.
